-- Court Hears China's First HIV-Status Job-Discrimination Suit, Xinhua Says
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2010-10-13T17:10:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-13/court-hears-china-s-first-hiv-status-job-discrimination-suit-xinhua-says.html
A court in China’s eastern province
of Anhui is hearing the country’s first employment-
discrimination case based on HIV status, Xinhua News Agency
said, citing proceedings in court.  The plaintiff, identified by the pseudonym Xiao Wu, is
seeking redress because he was denied a teaching job by Anqing
city’s education department for being HIV positive, Xinhua
reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  